shri ram bhakta hanuman ( hanuman , the worshipper of lord rama ) is a 1948 hindi religious film produced and directed by homi wadia for basant pictures .   the story was adapted from valmiki ’s ramayana by shivram vashikar and the dialogues were written by p. c. joshi .   s. n. tripathi not only provided music for the film but acted the main role of hanuman .   the film starred trilok kapoor , s. n. tripathi , sona chatterjee , niranjan sharma and prabhash joshi .   the story taken from an episode of valmiki ramayana centre ’s around the abduction of sita by ravana , and hanuman ’s support to rama and lakshman in the battle against ravana .